─ test_pack_runtime_validation.py (100 lines)\n│   │   │   ├── test_pack_runtime_workspace.py (43 lines)\n│   │   │   ├── test_publish_runtime.py (346 lines)\n│   │   │   └── test_status_runtime.py  (282 lines)\n│   │   └── services/\n│   │       ├── test_agentcube_provider.py (151 lines)\n│   │       ├── test_docker_service.py  (424 lines)\n│   │       ├── test_k8s_provider.py    (426 lines)\n│   │       ├── test_metadata_model.py  (151 lines)\n│   │       └── test_metadata_service.py (262 lines)\n│   └── examples/\n│       ├── hello-agent/\n│       │   ├── agent_metadata.yaml\n│       │   ├── main.py\n│       │   └── requirements.txt\n│       ├── math-agent/\n│       │   ├── agent_metadata.yaml\n│       │   ├── main.py\n│       │   └── requirements.txt\n│       └── java-agent/\n│           ├── agent_metadata.yaml\n│           ├── pom.xml\n│           └── src/main/java/com/example/App.java\n│\n├── example/pcap_analyzer/               # Separate example project\n│   ├── pcap_analyzer.py\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   └── tests/\n│       ├── __init__.py\n│       ├── test_agents.py\n│       ├── test_pcap_analyzer.py\n│       └── test_sandbox_runner.py\n│\n├── integrations/dify-plugin/            # Dify plugin integration\n│   ├── main.py\n│   ├── __init__.py\n│   ├── provider/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── agentcube.py\n│   ├── tools/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── agentcube-code-interpreter.py\n│   └── tests/\n│       ├── test_manifest.py\n│       ├── test_provider.py\n│       └── test_tool.py\n│\n├── design.md                            # Root-level design doc\n├── changes/AR-001/ through AR-037/      # 37 change request design docs\n├── ci-cd/design.md\n├── cli-toolkit/design.md\n├── code-execution/design.md\n├── deployment/design.md\n├── idle-cleanup/design.md\n├── sandbox-orchestration/design.md\n├── session-routing/design.md\n├── session-store/design.md\n├── proposal.md\n├── project.md\n├── tasks.md\n├── test_spec.md\n├── delta-spec.md\n├── Makefile\n├── agentd/                              # Go-based agent daemon\n├── client-go/                           # Go client library\n├── docker/\n├── hack/\n├── manifests/\n├── pkg/\n├── test/\n└── testing/\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Python SDK Source Files (python-sdk/)\n\n#### `python-sdk/pyproject.toml`\n- Package name: `agentcube-sdk`, version `0.1.0`\n- Requires Python `>=3.9`\n- Dependencies: `requests`, `PyJWT>=2.0.0`, `cryptography`\n- Build system: setuptools\n\n#### `python-sdk/agentcube/__init__.py` (4 lines)\n- Exports: `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient`\n\n#### `python-sdk/agentcube/agent_runtime.py` (79 lines)\n- `AgentRuntimeClient` class: High-level client for Agent Runtime invocation\n- Bootstraps sessions and invokes agent workloads through the Router\n- Supports context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__`)\n- Methods: `invoke(payload)`, `close()`\n- Resolves `router_url` from argument or `ROUTER_URL` env var\n\n#### `python-sdk/agentcube/code_interpreter.py` (161 lines)\n- `CodeInterpreterClient` class: High-level client for Code Interpreter sessions\n- Creates/manages sessions via Workload Manager (control plane) and executes code via Router (data plane)\n- Methods: `execute_command()`, `run_code()`, `write_file()`, `upload_file()`, `download_file()`, `list_files()`, `stop()`\n- Supports context manager\n- Auto-cleanup on data plane init failure\n\n#### `python-sdk/agentcube/exceptions.py` (21 lines)\n- Exception hierarchy:\n  - `AgentCubeError(Exception)` -- base\n  - `CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError)` -- has `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`\n  - `SessionError(AgentCubeError)`\n  - `DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError)`\n\n#### `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/__init__.py` (9 lines)\n- Exports: `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n\n#### `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` (96 lines)\n- `ControlPlaneClient`: Client for Workload Manager control plane API\n- Resolves URL from argument or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var\n- Auth token from argument, or falls back to Kubernetes SA token file\n- Methods: `create_session()`, `delete_session()` (404 = success), `close()`\n- HTTP: POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter`, DELETE `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}`\n\n#### `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` (176 lines)\n- `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`: Client for Code Interpreter data plane via Router\n- Base URL: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/`\n- Session header: `x-agentcube-session-id`\n- Methods: `execute_command()`, `run_code()`, `write_file()`, `upload_file()`, `download_file()`, `list_files()`, `close()`\n- Raises `CommandExecutionError` on non-zero exit codes\n\n#### `python-sdk/agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` (80 lines)\n- `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`: Client for Agent Runtime data plane via Router\n- Base URL: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n- Methods: `bootstrap_session_id()` (GET, reads header), `invoke()` (POST with session header), `close()`\n\n#### `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/http.py` (14 lines)\n- `create_session()`: Creates `requests.Session` with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling (default pool: 10/10)\n\n#### `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/log.py` (17 lines)\n- `get_logger()`: Returns configured logger with StreamHandler\n\n#### `python-sdk/agentcube/utils/utils.py` (7 lines)\n- `read_token_from_file()`: Reads token from file, returns stripped content or `\"\"` on FileNotFoundError\n\n---\n\n### 3. CLI Source Files (cmd/cli/)\n\n#### `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml` (63 lines)\n- Package name: `agentcube`, version `0.1.0`\n- Requires Python `>=3.10`\n- Dependencies: `typer[all]`, `pydantic`, `pyyaml`, `httpx`, `docker`, `rich`, `packaging`, `importlib-resources`, `semver`\n- Optional deps: `k8s` (kubernetes), `dev` (pytest, ruff, mypy, pre-commit), `test` (pytest-mock, httpx-mock)\n- Entry point: `kubectl-agentcube = agentcube.cli.main:app`\n- Tool configs: pytest, ruff, mypy\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/__init__.py` (14 lines)\n- Version `0.1.0`, author `AgentCube Community`, email `agentcube@volcano.sh`\n- Exports: `app`, `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`, `PublishRuntime`, `InvokeRuntime`, `StatusRuntime`\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` (286 lines)\n- Typer-based CLI with commands: `pack`, `build`, `publish`, `invoke`, `status`\n- Rich progress indicators, error handling with optional tracebacks\n- `--version`, `--verbose` global options\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/models/pack_models.py` (53 lines)\n- `MetadataOptions` dataclass: CLI options mapping to AgentMetadata fields\n- `from_options()`: Factory method that filters unknown fields\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` (228 lines)\n- `PackRuntime`: Orchestrates workspace validation, metadata merging, Dockerfile generation\n- Supports Python and Java languages\n- Auto-generates Dockerfiles if missing\n- Infers entrypoint from workspace contents\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` (152 lines)\n- `BuildRuntime`: Orchestrates version increment, prerequisite validation, building, metadata update\n- Supports local (Docker) and cloud builds\n- Semantic version auto-increment\n- Version rollback on build failure\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` (224 lines)\n- `PublishRuntime`: Deploys agents to Kubernetes\n- Two providers: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) and `k8s` (Deployment + Service)\n- Handles local image push and cloud image resolution\n- Validates NodePort range (30000-32767)\n- Waits for deployment readiness with timeout\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` (153 lines)\n- `InvokeRuntime`: Invokes deployed agents via HTTP\n- Provider-aware: rewrites endpoint URL for AgentRuntime CR type\n- Adds `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header when session_id exists in metadata\n- Uses `httpx.AsyncClient`\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` (101 lines)\n- `StatusRuntime`: Checks deployed agent status\n- Provider-aware: CR status vs. K8s deployment status\n- Returns structured status dicts\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` (147 lines)\n- `AgentMetadata`: Pydantic model with validators for language (python/java), build_mode (local/cloud), port (1-65535)\n- `MetadataService`: Loads/saves/updates metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml`\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` (221 lines)\n- `DockerService`: Docker daemon interaction\n- Methods: `check_docker_available()`, `build_image()`, `get_image_info()`, `push_image()`, `remove_image()`, `_docker_login_sdk()`, `_tag_image_sdk()`\n- Human-readable size formatting\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` (347 lines)\n- `KubernetesProvider`: Standard K8s Deployment + NodePort Service\n- Methods: `deploy_agent()`, `wait_for_deployment_ready()`, `get_agent_status()`, `update_agent()`, `delete_agent()`\n- Graceful 404 handling on updates/deletes\n\n#### `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` (253 lines)\n- `AgentCubeProvider`: AgentRuntime Custom Resource deployment\n- CRD: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/agentruntimes`\n- Methods: `deploy_agent_runtime()`, `update_agent_runtime()`, `delete_agent_runtime()`, `get_agent_runtime()`\n- Name sanitization (lowercase, max 63 chars, valid K8s name chars)\n\n---\n\n### 4. Test Files and Status\n\n#### Python SDK Tests (7 test files, ~2,708 lines total)\n| File | Lines | Coverage |\n|------|-------|----------|\n| `test_agent_runtime.py` | 837 | Data plane client, AgentRuntimeClient init/session/invoke/close/context manager/integration |\n| `test_code_interpreter.py` | 635 | Init, data plane failure cleanup, context manager, stop, execute_command, run_code, file ops, integration |\n| `test_control_plane.py` | 370 | Constructor/URL resolution, create_session, delete_session, close, session reuse |\n| `test_data_plane.py` | 641 | Constructor/base URL, _request, execute_command, run_code, write_file, upload_file, download_file, list_files, close |\n| `test_exceptions.py` | 77 | Exception hierarchy, attributes, message format, subclass relationships |\n| `test_imports.py` | 55 | Package imports, `__all__` exports validation |\n| `test_utils.py` | 93 | create_session, read_token_from_file, get_logger |\n\n#### CLI Tests (17+ test files, ~3,500+ lines total)\n| Category | Files | Coverage |\n|----------|-------|----------|\n| Services | 5 files | AgentCubeProvider, DockerService, K8sProvider, MetadataService, AgentMetadata model |\n| Runtime | 9+ files | BuildRuntime, PackRuntime (validation/workspace/entrypoint/overrides/metadata), PublishRuntime, InvokeRuntime, StatusRuntime |\n| CLI | 1+ files | build_command (default options, custom workspace, all options, success output, error handling, help) |\n| Models | 1 file | MetadataOptions defaults, from_options, unknown field filtering |\n| Integration | 1 file | Build e2e (local build, unpackaged error, CLI overrides, cloud build, invalid workspace, version increment, metadata update) |\n\nTests use `pytest` with `unittest.mock` for mocking. The SDK tests use `mocker` fixture from `pytest-mock`. One integration test is marked `@pytest.mark.skip(reason=\"Requires Docker daemon\")`.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Spec File: `python-sdk/design.md`\n\nLocated at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/design.md` (314 lines)\n\nThis is a comprehensive design document covering:\n- Package layout table mapping every file to its role\n- Public exports for `agentcube/__init__.py` and `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n- Configuration resolution strategy (no single Configuration class; defaults distributed across clients)\n- Full API signatures for all classes: `CodeInterpreterClient`, `AgentRuntimeClient`, `ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`\n- HTTP endpoint tables for control plane and data plane APIs\n- Exception hierarchy\n- Dependencies from pyproject.toml\n\n---\n\n### 6. Configuration Files\n\n#### `python-sdk/pyproject.toml`\n- `agentcube-sdk` v0.1.0, Python >=3.9\n- Deps: requests, PyJWT>=2.0.0, cryptography\n- setuptools build\n\n#### `cmd/cli/pyproject.toml`\n- `agentcube` v0.1.0, Python >=3.10\n- Deps: typer[all], pydantic, pyyaml, httpx, docker, rich, packaging, importlib-resources, semver\n- Optional: k8s (kubernetes>=28.0.0), dev (pytest, ruff, mypy, pre-commit), test (pytest-mock, httpx-mock)\n- Entry point: `kubectl-agentcube`\n- Tool configs for pytest, ruff (line-length 120, py310), mypy (py310)\n\n---\n\n### 7. Example Agents\n\n#### `hello-agent/main.py` (3 lines)\n- Simple print statement: `\"Hello from AgentCube!\"`\n\n#### `math-agent/main.py` (20 lines)\n- Math expression evaluator using `eval()` with restricted builtins\n- CLI usage: `python main.py <expression>`\n\n#### `java-agent/`\n- Maven project with `pom.xml` and `App.java`\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThe agentcube project consists of two main Python packages:\n\n1. **Python SDK** (`python-sdk/`): A client library for interacting with AgentCube's Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime services. It provides high-level clients that handle session management, code execution, file operations, and agent invocation through control plane and data plane APIs.\n\n2. **CLI Tool** (`cmd/cli/`): A developer tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for the full AI agent lifecycle: packaging workspaces, building container images (local Docker or cloud), publishing to Kubernetes (as either AgentRuntime CRs or standard Deployments), invoking deployed agents, and checking status.\n\nThe project has extensive test coverage with well-organized unit tests for every component, plus integration/e2e tests.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_284f78d1fffefa0ki28glMPRpY","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project","time":{"start":1775885644510,"end":1775885917673}}}}
