{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885926956,"sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0cbd56001BodGm0CVjeyiXy","messageID":"msg_d7b0cb7b9001v6CJIt7xuuU3uL","sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_186bce1f616244fc89aedaca","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用 — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: This AR covers the PCAP (Packet Capture) analyzer example application for the AgentCube Python SDK. It demonstrates the complete workflow of file upload, remote code execution, and result download using `CodeInterpreterClient`, providing users with a runnable network analysis reference implementation.\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 System Context\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                         User / Developer                             │\n14: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n15: │  │              examples/pcap_analyzer/                         │    │\n16: │  │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n17: │  │  │              pcap_analyzer.py                         │  │    │\n18: │  │  │         (CLI Example Script)                          │  │    │\n19: │  │  └──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘  │    │\n20: │  │                         │                                   │    │\n21: │  │  ┌──────────────────────▼───────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n22: │  │  │         CodeInterpreterClient (SDK)                   │  │    │\n23: │  │  │   (upload_file, run_code, execute_command,            │  │    │\n24: │  │  │    download_file, list_files, context manager)        │  │    │\n25: │  │  └──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘  │    │\n26: │  └─────────────────────────┼──────────────────────────────────┘    │\n27: └────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────┘\n28:                              │\n29:                              ▼\n30: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n31: │                    AgentCube Platform                                │\n32: │  ┌──────────────────────┐          ┌────────────────────────────┐   │\n33: │  │  Control Plane       │◄────────►│  Code Interpreter Pod      │   │\n34: │  │  (Session Lifecycle) │         │  (Python 3.10+, scapy)     │   │\n35: │  └──────────────────────┘          └────────────────────────────┘   │\n36: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### 1.3 Design Principles\n40: \n41: - **Example-only**: No modifications to SDK core code; uses only public API (`__all__` exports)\n42: - **CLI script style**: Consistent with existing examples (`basic_usage.py`, `agent_runtime_usage.py`)\n43: - **Self-contained**: Single script with embedded analysis logic via `run_code`\n44: - **Graceful degradation**: `tshark` as optional enhancement with conditional detection\n45: - **Small footprint**: Sample PCAP < 1MB, no chunked upload complexity\n46: \n47: ### 1.4 Package Structure\n48: \n49: ```\n50: sdk-python/\n51: ├── examples/\n52: │   ├── basic_usage.py                      # Existing\n53: │   ├── agent_runtime_usage.py              # Existing\n54: │   └── pcap_analyzer/                      # NEW (this AR)\n55: │       ├── pcap_analyzer.py                # Main example script\n56: │       ├── README.md                       # Usage guide\n57: │       ├── requirements.txt                # Example dependencies\n58: │       └── sample_traffic.pcap             # Sample PCAP file (< 1MB)\n59: └── ...\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### 1.5 Dependencies\n63: \n64: | Dependency | Scope | Purpose |\n65: |------------|-------|---------|\n66: | `agentcube-sdk` | Local import | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n67: | `scapy` | Remote sandbox | PCAP parsing (installed via `run_code` if needed) |\n68: | `tshark` (optional) | Remote sandbox | CLI filtering tool (conditional detection) |\n69: \n70: **No new Python package dependencies** — the example script uses only stdlib + `agentcube-sdk`.\n71: \n72: ---\n73: \n74: ## 2. Data Structures\n75: \n76: ### 2.1 Analysis Result Format (JSON)\n77: \n78: The remote analysis script produces JSON output with the following structure:\n79: \n80: ```json\n81: {\n82:   \"file_name\": \"sample_traffic.pcap\",\n83:   \"total_packets\": 1234,\n84:   \"duration_seconds\": 60.5,\n85:   \"protocols\": {\n86:     \"TCP\": 800,\n87:     \"UDP\": 300,\n88:     \"ICMP\": 50,\n89:     \"HTTP\": 60,\n90:     \"DNS\": 24\n91:   },\n92:   \"top_source_ips\": [\n93:     {\"ip\": \"192.168.1.100\", \"count\": 500},\n94:     {\"ip\": \"10.0.0.1\", \"count\": 300}\n95:   ],\n96:   \"top_dest_ips\": [\n97:     {\"ip\": \"8.8.8.8\", \"count\": 200},\n98:     {\"ip\": \"1.1.1.1\", \"count\": 150}\n99:   ],\n100:   \"timeline\": [\n101:     {\"timestamp\": 1699000000.0, \"packets\": 100},\n102:     {\"timestamp\": 1699000010.0, \"packets\": 150}\n103:   ],\n104:   \"errors\": []\n105: }\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ### 2.2 CLI Arguments\n109: \n110: | Argument | Type | Default | Description |\n111: |----------|------|---------|-------------|\n112: | `--pcap-file` | `str` | `sample_traffic.pcap` | Path to PCAP file to analyze |\n113: | `--output` | `str` | `analysis_result.json` | Local path for result output |\n114: | `--top-n` | `int` | `10` | Number of top IPs to report |\n115: | `--timeline-interval` | `float` | `10.0` | Timeline bucket size in seconds |\n116: | `--verbose` | `flag` | `False` | Enable verbose logging |\n117: \n118: ### 2.3 Environment Variables\n119: \n120: | Variable | Required | Description |\n121: |----------|----------|-------------|\n122: | `ROUTER_URL` | Yes | Router endpoint URL |\n123: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | No | Control plane URL (defaults to SDK default) |\n124: | `AUTH_TOKEN` | No | Auth token (falls back to SA token file) |\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 3. Interfaces\n129: \n130: ### 3.1 Main Script Entry Point\n131: \n132: ```python\n133: #!/usr/bin/env python3\n134: \"\"\"PCAP Analyzer Example — demonstrates CodeInterpreterClient workflow.\"\"\"\n135: \n136: import argparse\n137: import json\n138: import os\n139: import sys\n140: \n141: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n142: \n143: \n144: def main():\n145:     parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"PCAP Analyzer Example\")\n146:     parser.add_argument(\"--pcap-file\", default=\"sample_traffic.pcap\")\n147:     parser.add_argument(\"--output\", default=\"analysis_result.json\")\n148:     parser.add_argument(\"--top-n\", type=int, default=10)\n149:     parser.add_argument(\"--timeline-interval\", type=float, default=10.0)\n150:     parser.add_argument(\"--verbose\", action=\"store_true\")\n151:     args = parser.parse_args()\n152: \n153:     router_url = os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n154:     if not router_url:\n155:         print(\"Error: ROUTER_URL environment variable is required\", file=sys.stderr)\n156:         sys.exit(1)\n157: \n158:     analyze_pcap(\n159:         pcap_file=args.pcap_file,\n160:         output_file=args.output,\n161:         top_n=args.top_n,\n162:         timeline_interval=args.timeline_interval,\n163:         verbose=args.verbose,\n164:         router_url=router_url,\n165:     )\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ### 3.2 Core Analysis Function\n169: \n170: ```python\n171: def analyze_pcap(\n172:     pcap_file: str,\n173:     output_file: str,\n174:     top_n: int,\n175:     timeline_interval: float,\n176:     verbose: bool,\n177:     router_url: str,\n178: ) -> None:\n179:     \"\"\"Upload PCAP, run analysis, download results.\"\"\"\n180: ```\n181: \n182: **Workflow:**\n183: \n184: 1. Validate PCAP file exists locally\n185: 2. Create `CodeInterpreterClient` (context manager)\n186: 3. Upload PCAP file to remote sandbox (`upload_file`)\n187: 4. Install `scapy` if needed (`run_code` with `pip install`)\n188: 5. Execute analysis script (`run_code` with embedded Python)\n189: 6. Optionally run `tshark` commands (`execute_command` if available)\n190: 7. Write results to remote file (`write_file` or script output)\n191: 8. Download results (`download_file`)\n192: 9. Print summary to console\n193: 10. Context manager cleanup (`__exit__` → `stop()`)\n194: \n195: ### 3.3 Embedded Analysis Script (via `run_code`)\n196: \n197: The analysis logic is passed as a Python string to `run_code`. It uses `scapy` to parse the PCAP file:\n198: \n199: ```python\n200: ANALYSIS_SCRIPT = \"\"\"\n201: from scapy.all import rdpcap, IP, TCP, UDP, ICMP, DNS, Raw\n202: import json\n203: import sys\n204: from collections import Counter\n205: \n206: def analyze_pcap(pcap_path, top_n=10, timeline_interval=10.0):\n207:     packets = rdpcap(pcap_path)\n208:     \n209:     result = {\n210:         \"file_name\": pcap_path,\n211:         \"total_packets\": len(packets),\n212:         \"duration_seconds\": 0.0,\n213:         \"protocols\": {},\n214:         \"top_source_ips\": [],\n215:         \"top_dest_ips\": [],\n216:         \"timeline\": [],\n217:         \"errors\": []\n218:     }\n219:     \n220:     if not packets:\n221:         return result\n222:     \n223:     # Duration\n224:     first_ts = float(packets[0].time)\n225:     last_ts = float(packets[-1].time)\n226:     result[\"duration_seconds\"] = last_ts - first_ts\n227:     \n228:     # Protocol distribution\n229:     proto_counts = Counter()\n230:     src_ips = Counter()\n231:     dst_ips = Counter()\n232:     timeline_buckets = Counter()\n233:     \n234:     for pkt in packets:\n235:         ts = float(pkt.time)\n236:         bucket = int((ts - first_ts) / timeline_interval) * timeline_interval + first_ts\n237:         \n238:         if pkt.haslayer(TCP):\n239:             proto_counts[\"TCP\"] += 1\n240:             if pkt.haslayer(Raw):\n241:                 proto_counts[\"HTTP\"] += 1  # Simplified HTTP detection\n242:         elif pkt.haslayer(UDP):\n243:             if pkt.haslayer(DNS):\n244:                 proto_counts[\"DNS\"] += 1\n245:             else:\n246:                 proto_counts[\"UDP\"] += 1\n247:         elif pkt.haslayer(ICMP):\n248:             proto_counts[\"ICMP\"] += 1\n249:         else:\n250:             proto_counts[\"Other\"] += 1\n251:         \n252:         if pkt.haslayer(IP):\n253:             src_ips[pkt[IP].src] += 1\n254:             dst_ips[pkt[IP].dst] += 1\n255:         \n256:         timeline_buckets[bucket] += 1\n257:     \n258:     result[\"protocols\"] = dict(proto_counts)\n259:     result[\"top_source_ips\"] = [\n260:         {\"ip\": ip, \"count\": count}\n261:         for ip, count in src_ips.most_common(top_n)\n262:     ]\n263:     result[\"top_dest_ips\"] = [\n264:         {\"ip\": ip, \"count\": count}\n265:         for ip, count in dst_ips.most_common(top_n)\n266:     ]\n267:     result[\"timeline\"] = sorted([\n268:         {\"timestamp\": ts, \"packets\": count}\n269:         for ts, count in timeline_buckets.items()\n270:     ], key=lambda x: x[\"timestamp\"])\n271:     \n272:     return result\n273: \n274: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n275:     pcap_file = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else \"/tmp/uploaded.pcap\"\n276:     top_n = int(sys.argv[2]) if len(sys.argv) > 2 else 10\n277:     interval = float(sys.argv[3]) if len(sys.argv) > 3 else 10.0\n278:     \n279:     result = analyze_pcap(pcap_file, top_n, interval)\n280:     print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n281: \"\"\"\n282: ```\n283: \n284: ### 3.4 Optional tshark Enhancement\n285: \n286: ```python\n287: def check_tshark_available(client: CodeInterpreterClient) -> bool:\n288:     \"\"\"Check if tshark is available in the remote sandbox.\"\"\"\n289:     try:\n290:         result = client.execute_command(\"which tshark\")\n291:         return result.strip() != \"\"\n292:     except Exception:\n293:         return False\n294: \n295: \n296: def run_tshark_filter(client: CodeInterpreterClient, pcap_path: str, filter_expr: str) -> str:\n297:     \"\"\"Run tshark with a display filter on the remote PCAP.\"\"\"\n298:     cmd = f\"tshark -r {pcap_path} -Y '{filter_expr}' -T fields -e ip.src -e ip.dst -e frame.len\"\n299:     return client.execute_command(cmd)\n300: ```\n301: \n302: ---\n303: \n304: ## 4. Error Handling\n305: \n306: ### 4.1 Error Classification\n307: \n308: | Scenario | Exception | Handling |\n309: |----------|-----------|----------|\n310: | PCAP file not found locally | `FileNotFoundError` | Print error, exit 1 |\n311: | `ROUTER_URL` not set | `ValueError` | Print error, exit 1 |\n312: | Upload failure | SDK exception | Propagate with context |\n313: | `scapy` installation failure | `CommandExecutionError` | Retry or warn, continue |\n314: | Analysis script error | `CommandExecutionError` | Print stderr, exit 1 |\n315: | Result download failure | SDK exception | Propagate with context |\n316: | Invalid JSON output | `json.JSONDecodeError` | Print raw output, warn |\n317: | Context manager cleanup failure | SDK exception | Log warning, exit |\n318: \n319: ### 4.2 Error Recovery Strategy\n320: \n321: ```python\n322: def analyze_pcap(...):\n323:     # Pre-flight checks\n324:     if not os.path.exists(pcap_file):\n325:         print(f\"Error: PCAP file not found: {pcap_file}\", file=sys.stderr)\n326:         sys.exit(1)\n327:     \n328:     # Context manager ensures cleanup\n329:     with CodeInterpreterClient(\n330:         name=\"pcap-analyzer\",\n331:         router_url=router_url,\n332:         verbose=verbose,\n333:     ) as client:\n334:         try:\n335:             # Upload\n336:             remote_path = f\"/tmp/{os.path.basename(pcap_file)}\"\n337:             client.upload_file(pcap_file, remote_path)\n338:             \n339:             # Install scapy (best effort)\n340:             try:\n341:                 client.run_code(\"python\", \"import scapy\")\n342:             except Exception:\n343:                 if verbose:\n344:                     print(\"Installing scapy in remote sandbox...\")\n345:                 client.run_code(\"python\", \"import subprocess; subprocess.run(['pip', 'install', 'scapy'])\")\n346:             \n347:             # Run analysis\n348:             script = ANALYSIS_SCRIPT.replace(\"TOP_N_PLACEHOLDER\", str(top_n))\n349:             result_json = client.run_code(\"python\", script)\n350:             result = json.loads(result_json)\n351:             \n352:             # Optional tshark\n353:             if check_tshark_available(client):\n354:                 tshark_result = run_tshark_filter(client, remote_path, \"tcp\")\n355:                 result[\"tshark_tcp_summary\"] = tshark_result\n356:             \n357:             # Save results locally\n358:             with open(output_file, \"w\") as f:\n359:                 json.dump(result, f, indent=2)\n360:             \n361:             # Print summary\n362:             print_analysis_summary(result)\n363:             \n364:         except Exception as e:\n365:             print(f\"Analysis failed: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n366:             sys.exit(1)\n367: ```\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ## 5. Implementation Notes\n372: \n373: ### 5.1 Remote Sandbox Assumptions\n374: \n375: | Assumption | Verification | Fallback |\n376: |------------|--------------|----------|\n377: | Python 3.10+ available | `run_code(\"python\", \"import sys; print(sys.version)\")` | Error if not met |\n378: | `pip install` works | Try `pip install scapy` | Pre-install in sandbox image |\n379: | `/tmp` writable | `execute_command(\"touch /tmp/test && rm /tmp/test\")` | Use alternative path |\n380: | `tshark` available (optional) | `execute_command(\"which tshark\")` | Skip tshark features |\n381: \n382: ### 5.2 Script Size Considerations\n383: \n384: The embedded `ANALYSIS_SCRIPT` is ~60 lines of Python. For `run_code`, this is passed as a string argument. If the script grows significantly, consider:\n385: \n386: 1. Using `write_file` to upload the script first, then `execute_command` to run it\n387: 2. Splitting into multiple `run_code` calls\n388: \n389: Current approach (inline) is preferred for simplicity and demonstration purposes.\n390: \n391: ### 5.3 Timeout Configuration\n392: \n393: | Operation | Timeout | Rationale |\n394: |-----------|---------|-----------|\n395: | PCAP upload | Default (120s) | < 1MB file, should be fast |\n396: | scapy install | 60s | Network-dependent |\n397: | Analysis execution | 120s | Depends on PCAP size |\n398: | tshark filter | 60s | Optional enhancement |\n399: | Result download | Default (120s) | JSON output, small |\n400: \n401: ### 5.4 Sample PCAP Generation\n402: \n403: The `sample_traffic.pcap` file can be generated using `scapy`:\n404: \n405: ```python\n406: # scripts/generate_sample_pcap.py\n407: from scapy.all import IP, TCP, UDP, ICMP, wrpcap, Ether\n408: import random\n409: \n410: packets = []\n411: base_time = 1699000000.0\n412: \n413: for i in range(100):\n414:     src = f\"192.168.1.{random.randint(1, 254)}\"\n415:     dst = f\"10.0.0.{random.randint(1, 254)}\"\n416:     \n417:     if i % 3 == 0:\n418:         pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / TCP(sport=random.randint(1024, 65535), dport=80)\n419:     elif i % 3 == 1:\n420:         pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / UDP(sport=53, dport=random.randint(1024, 65535))\n421:     else:\n422:         pkt = IP(src=src, dst=dst) / ICMP()\n423:     \n424:     pkt.time = base_time + i * 0.5\n425:     packets.append(pkt)\n426: \n427: wrpcap(\"sample_traffic.pcap\", packets)\n428: ```\n429: \n430: ---\n431: \n432: ## 6. Testing Strategy\n433: \n434: ### 6.1 Test Categories\n435: \n436: | Category | Scope | Approach |\n437: |----------|-------|----------|\n438: | Script validation | Syntax, imports | `python -m py_compile pcap_analyzer.py` |\n439: | Unit tests | Analysis logic | Run embedded script locally with test PCAP |\n440: | Integration tests | SDK interaction | Mock `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n441: | Manual E2E | Full workflow | Run against real AgentCube platform |\n442: \n443: ### 6.2 Key Test Scenarios\n444: \n445: | Test Name | Description |\n446: |-----------|-------------|\n447: | `test_script_syntax` | Embedded analysis script compiles without errors |\n448: | `test_analysis_with_sample_pcap` | Run analysis on sample_traffic.pcap, verify JSON structure |\n449: | `test_empty_pcap` | Handle PCAP with 0 packets gracefully |\n450: | `test_cli_argument_parsing` | Verify argparse handles all flags correctly |\n451: | `test_missing_router_url` | Exit with error if ROUTER_URL not set |\n452: | `test_missing_pcap_file` | Exit with error if PCAP file not found |\n453: | `test_mocked_sdk_workflow` | Mock CodeInterpreterClient, verify call sequence |\n454: \n455: ### 6.3 Mocked SDK Test Example\n456: \n457: ```python\n458: from unittest.mock import MagicMock, patch\n459: \n460: def test_mocked_sdk_workflow():\n461:     \"\"\"Verify the expected SDK call sequence.\"\"\"\n462:     mock_client = MagicMock()\n463:     mock_client.__enter__ = MagicMock(return_value=mock_client)\n464:     mock_client.__exit__ = MagicMock(return_value=False)\n465:     \n466:     mock_client.run_code.return_value = json.dumps({\n467:         \"total_packets\": 100,\n468:         \"protocols\": {\"TCP\": 60, \"UDP\": 40},\n469:         \"top_source_ips\": [],\n470:         \"top_dest_ips\": [],\n471:         \"timeline\": [],\n472:         \"errors\": []\n473:     })\n474:     \n475:     with patch(\"agentcube.CodeInterpreterClient\", return_value=mock_client):\n476:         # Run analyze_pcap with test fixtures\n477:         # Verify call sequence:\n478:         # 1. upload_file called\n479:         # 2. run_code called for analysis\n480:         # 3. download_file or result handling\n481:         pass\n482: ```\n483: \n484: ---\n485: \n486: ## 7. Usage Examples\n487: \n488: ### 7.1 Basic Usage\n489: \n490: ```bash\n491: export ROUTER_URL=\"http://router:8080\"\n492: cd examples/pcap_analyzer\n493: python pcap_analyzer.py --pcap-file sample_traffic.pcap\n494: ```\n495: \n496: **Expected output:**\n497: \n498: ```\n499: PCAP Analysis Complete\n500: =====================\n501: File: sample_traffic.pcap\n502: Total packets: 100\n503: Duration: 49.50s\n504: \n505: Protocol Distribution:\n506:   TCP:  60 (60.0%)\n507:   UDP:  40 (40.0%)\n508: \n509: Top Source IPs:\n510:   192.168.1.105: 15 packets\n511:   192.168.1.200: 12 packets\n512:   192.168.1.50:  10 packets\n513: \n514: Top Destination IPs:\n515:   10.0.0.1: 25 packets\n516:   10.0.0.5: 20 packets\n517: \n518: Results saved to: analysis_result.json\n519: ```\n520: \n521: ### 7.2 Custom Parameters\n522: \n523: ```bash\n524: python pcap_analyzer.py \\\n525:   --pcap-file /path/to/capture.pcap \\\n526:   --output /path/to/report.json \\\n527:   --top-n 20 \\\n528:   --timeline-interval 5.0 \\\n529:   --verbose\n530: ```\n531: \n532: ### 7.3 With tshark (if available)\n533: \n534: When `tshark` is detected in the remote sandbox, additional filtering output is included:\n535: \n536: ```\n537: tshark TCP Filter Results:\n538:   192.168.1.100 -> 10.0.0.1: 1500 bytes\n539:   192.168.1.100 -> 10.0.0.1: 1200 bytes\n540:   ...\n541: ```\n542: \n543: ---\n544: \n545: ## 8. README Content\n546: \n547: The `examples/pcap_analyzer/README.md` will contain:\n548: \n549: ```markdown\n550: # PCAP Analyzer Example\n551: \n552: Demonstrates the complete CodeInterpreterClient workflow:\n553: upload → analyze → download.\n554: \n555: ## Prerequisites\n556: \n557: - Python 3.10+\n558: - `agentcube-sdk` installed\n559: - Access to AgentCube platform (ROUTER_URL)\n560: \n561: ## Quick Start\n562: \n563: ```bash\n564: export ROUTER_URL=\"http://router:8080\"\n565: python pcap_analyzer.py --pcap-file sample_traffic.pcap\n566: ```\n567: \n568: ## Analysis Features\n569: \n570: - Protocol distribution (TCP/UDP/ICMP/DNS/HTTP)\n571: - Top N source and destination IPs\n572: - Traffic timeline overview\n573: - Optional tshark filtering (if available in sandbox)\n574: \n575: ## Output\n576: \n577: Results are saved as JSON and printed as a summary to stdout.\n578: ```\n\n(End of file - total 578 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers the PCAP (Packet Capture) analyzer example application for the AgentCube Python SDK. It demonstrates the complete workflow of file upload, remote code execution, and result download using `CodeInterpreterClient`, providing users with a runnable network analysis reference implementation.\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         User / Developer                             │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │              examples/pcap_analyzer/                         │    │\n│  │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n│  │  │              pcap_analyzer.py                         │  │    │\n│  │  │         (CLI Example Script)                          │  │    │\n│  │  └──────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘  │    │\n│  │                         │                                   │    │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/design.md","time":{"start":1775885926940,"end":1775885926953}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885928277,"sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0cc2ab001iXdx3i6xvyyNkW","messageID":"msg_d7b0cb7b9001v6CJIt7xuuU3uL","sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_03a6c537e1f8488f9081cb63","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Changes\n4: \n5: <!-- List of additions, modifications, deletions -->\n6: \n7: ### Additions\n8: \n9: <!-- New files, functions, features -->\n10: \n11: ### Modifications\n12: \n13: <!-- Existing code that will change -->\n14: \n15: ### Deletions\n16: \n17: <!-- Code to be removed -->\n\n(End of file - total 17 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037 — Delta Spec\n\n## Changes\n\n<!-- List of additions, modifications, deletions -->\n\n### Additions\n\n<!-- New files, functions, features -->\n\n### Modifications\n\n<!-- Existing code that will change -->\n\n### Deletions\n\n<!-- Code to be removed -->","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775885928269,"end":1775885928276}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885929646,"sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0cc7dc001b5PO2mdhaXGSb7","messageID":"msg_d7b0cb7b9001v6CJIt7xuuU3uL","sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a2e50cfdbbf440309560a5b5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: import argparse\n2: import json\n3: import os\n4: import sys\n5: import time\n6: import tempfile\n7: from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n8: \n9: from fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\n10: from pydantic import BaseModel\n11: import uvicorn\n12: \n13: from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\n14: from langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\n15: from langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, AIMessage\n16: \n17: # Configuration constants\n18: API_KEY = os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\")\n19: API_BASE_URL = os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_BASE\", \"https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1\")\n20: MODEL_NAME = os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_MODEL\", \"Qwen/QwQ-32B\")\n21: CODEINTERPRETER_NAME = os.environ.get(\"CODEINTERPRETER_NAME\", \"my-interpreter\")\n22: SANDBOX_NAMESPACE = os.environ.get(\"SANDBOX_NAMESPACE\", \"default\")\n23: SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC = int(os.environ.get(\"SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC\", \"5\"))\n24: SERVER_HOST = \"0.0.0.0\"\n25: SERVER_PORT = 8000\n26: SERVER_RELOAD = True\n27: \n28: # Global agent instances\n29: PLANNER = None\n30: REPORTER = None\n31: \n32: \n33: class SandboxRunner:\n34:     \"\"\"Executes commands and manages files in an AgentCube sandbox.\"\"\"\n35: \n36:     def __init__(\n37:         self,\n38:         name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n39:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n40:         warmup_sec: int = 5,\n41:     ):\n42:         self.name = name\n43:         self.namespace = namespace\n44:         self.warmup_sec = warmup_sec\n45:         self.client = None\n46: \n47:     def _ensure_client(self):\n48:         if self.client is None:\n49:             from agentcube.code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n50:             self.client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n51:                 name=self.name,\n52:                 namespace=self.namespace,\n53:             )\n54:             if self.warmup_sec > 0:\n55:                 time.sleep(self.warmup_sec)\n56: \n57:     def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> bool:\n58:         try:\n59:             self._ensure_client()\n60:             self.client.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)\n61:             return True\n62:         except Exception:\n63:             return False\n64: \n65:     def upload_bytes(self, data: bytes, remote_path: str) -> bool:\n66:         try:\n67:             self._ensure_client()\n68:             with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(delete=False, mode=\"wb\") as f:\n69:                 f.write(data)\n70:                 tmp_path = f.name\n71:             self.client.upload_file(tmp_path, remote_path)\n72:             os.unlink(tmp_path)\n73:             return True\n74:         except Exception:\n75:             return False\n76: \n77:     def run(self, command: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n78:         self._ensure_client()\n79:         try:\n80:             output = self.client.execute_command(command)\n81:             return {\n82:                 \"success\": True,\n83:                 \"output\": output,\n84:                 \"error\": None,\n85:                 \"exit_code\": 0,\n86:             }\n87:         except Exception as e:\n88:             return {\n89:                 \"success\": False,\n90:                 \"output\": None,\n91:                 \"error\": str(e),\n92:                 \"exit_code\": 1,\n93:             }\n94: \n95:     def stop(self):\n96:         if self.client is not None:\n97:             try:\n98:                 self.client.stop()\n99:             except Exception:\n100:                 pass\n101:             self.client = None\n102: \n103: \n104: def build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt: str):\n105:     \"\"\"Build a ReAct agent with the given LLM and system prompt.\"\"\"\n106:     return create_react_agent(llm, [], prompt=system_prompt)\n107: \n108: \n109: def invoke_react_agent(agent, user_text: str) -> str:\n110:     \"\"\"Invoke a ReAct agent with user text and return the response.\"\"\"\n111:     response = agent.invoke({\"messages\": [HumanMessage(content=user_text)]})\n112:     if \"messages\" in response:\n113:         last_msg = response[\"messages\"][-1]\n114:         if hasattr(last_msg, \"content\"):\n115:             return last_msg.content\n116:     return str(response)\n117: \n118: \n119: def build_planner_agent(llm):\n120:     \"\"\"Build a planner agent for generating analysis scripts.\"\"\"\n121:     system_prompt = (\n122:         \"You are a PCAP analysis planner. Given a description of a PCAP file, \"\n123:         \"generate a Python script that analyzes the PCAP file using scapy or similar tools. \"\n124:         \"The script should read the PCAP file from /workspace/input.pcap, \"\n125:         \"perform analysis, and print results to stdout. \"\n126:         \"Output ONLY the Python script, no explanations.\"\n127:     )\n128:     return build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt)\n129: \n130: \n131: def build_reporter_agent(llm):\n132:     \"\"\"Build a reporter agent for generating analysis reports.\"\"\"\n133:     system_prompt = (\n134:         \"You are a PCAP analysis reporter. Given execution results from a PCAP analysis script, \"\n135:         \"generate a comprehensive report summarizing the findings. \"\n136:         \"Include key statistics, notable patterns, and any anomalies detected.\"\n137:     )\n138:     return build_react_agent(llm, system_prompt)\n139: \n140: \n141: def _plan_script(agent, pcap_local_path: str) -> str:\n142:     \"\"\"Generate an analysis script using the planner agent.\"\"\"\n143:     prompt = (\n144:         f\"Generate a Python script to analyze the PCAP file located at {pcap_local_path}. \"\n145:         \"The script should read the PCAP, extract key information (protocols, IPs, ports, packet sizes), \"\n146:         \"and print a summary. Output only the script code.\"\n147:     )\n148:     return invoke_react_agent(agent, prompt)\n149: \n150: \n151: def _repair_script(agent, prev_script: str, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str:\n152:     \"\"\"Repair a failed script using the planner agent.\"\"\"\n153:     error_info = \"\"\n154:     for r in results:\n155:         if r.get(\"error\"):\n156:             error_info += f\"\\nError: {r['error']}\"\n157:     prompt = (\n158:         f\"The following script failed during execution:\\n\\n{prev_script}\\n\\n\"\n159:         f\"Errors encountered:{error_info}\\n\\n\"\n160:         \"Please fix the script and output only the corrected Python code.\"\n161:     )\n162:     return invoke_react_agent(agent, prompt)\n163: \n164: \n165: def _execute_once_in_runner(\n166:     runner: SandboxRunner, pcap_local_path: str, script: str\n167: ) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]:\n168:     \"\"\"Upload PCAP and execute the script in the sandbox.\"\"\"\n169:     results = []\n170: \n171:     runner.upload_file(pcap_local_path, \"/workspace/input.pcap\")\n172: \n173:     with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(\n174:         delete=False, mode=\"w\", suffix=\".py\"\n175:     ) as f:\n176:         f.write(script)\n177:         script_path = f.name\n178: \n179:     try:\n180:         runner.upload_file(script_path, \"/workspace/analyze.py\")\n181:         result = runner.run(\"python3 /workspace/analyze.py\")\n182:         results.append(result)\n183:     finally:\n184:         os.unlink(script_path)\n185: \n186:     return results\n187: \n188: \n189: def _analyze_with_retries(\n190:     planner,\n191:     reporter,\n192:     runner: SandboxRunner,\n193:     pcap_local_path: str,\n194:     max_retries: int = 2,\n195: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n196:     \"\"\"Run analysis with planning, execution, and repair retries.\"\"\"\n197:     script = _plan_script(planner, pcap_local_path)\n198:     results = []\n199: \n200:     for attempt in range(max_retries + 1):\n201:         try:\n202:             results = _execute_once_in_runner(runner, pcap_local_path, script)\n203:             all_success = all(r.get(\"success\") for r in results)\n204:             if all_success:\n205:                 break\n206:         except Exception:\n207:             pass\n208: \n209:         if attempt < max_retries:\n210:             script = _repair_script(planner, script, results)\n211: \n212:     report = _report(reporter, results)\n213: \n214:     return {\n215:         \"script\": script,\n216:         \"results\": results,\n217:         \"report\": report,\n218:     }\n219: \n220: \n221: def _report(agent, results: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> str:\n222:     \"\"\"Generate a report from execution results using the reporter agent.\"\"\"\n223:     results_str = \"\\n\".join(str(r) for r in results)\n224:     prompt = (\n225:         f\"Based on the following PCAP analysis execution results, generate a report:\\n\\n{results_str}\"\n226:     )\n227:     return invoke_react_agent(agent, prompt)\n228: \n229: \n230: class AnalyzeResponse(BaseModel):\n231:     script: str\n232:     results: List[Dict[str, Any]]\n233:     report: str\n234: \n235: \n236: app = FastAPI(title=\"PCAP Analyzer — Env-Only Config\")\n237: \n238: \n239: @app.on_event(\"startup\")\n240: async def on_startup():\n241:     global PLANNER, REPORTER\n242: \n243:     if not API_KEY:\n244:         raise ValueError(\n245:             \"OPENAI_API_KEY environment variable is required. \"\n246:             \"Please set it before starting the application.\"\n247:         )\n248: \n249:     llm = ChatOpenAI(\n250:         openai_api_key=API_KEY,\n251:         openai_api_base=API_BASE_URL,\n252:         model_name=MODEL_NAME,\n253:     )\n254: \n255:     PLANNER = build_planner_agent(llm)\n256:     REPORTER = build_reporter_agent(llm)\n257: \n258: \n259: @app.post(\"/analyze\", response_model=AnalyzeResponse)\n260: async def analyze_endpoint(\n261:     pcap_file: UploadFile = File(None),\n262:     pcap_path: str = Form(None),\n263: ):\n264:     if pcap_file is None and pcap_path is None:\n265:         raise HTTPException(\n266:             status_code=400,\n267:             detail=\"Either pcap_file (upload) or pcap_path (form field) must be provided\",\n268:         )\n269: \n270:     local_path = None\n271:     try:\n272:         if pcap_file is not None:\n273:             with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(\n274:                 delete=False, suffix=\".pcap\"\n275:             ) as f:\n276:                 content = await pcap_file.read()\n277:                 f.write(content)\n278:                 local_path = f.name\n279:         else:\n280:             local_path = pcap_path\n281: \n282:         runner = SandboxRunner(\n283:             name=CODEINTERPRETER_NAME,\n284:             namespace=SANDBOX_NAMESPACE,\n285:             warmup_sec=SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC,\n286:         )\n287: \n288:         try:\n289:             analysis = _analyze_with_retries(\n290:                 planner=PLANNER,\n291:                 reporter=REPORTER,\n292:                 runner=runner,\n293:                 pcap_local_path=local_path,\n294:                 max_retries=2,\n295:             )\n296:         finally:\n297:             runner.stop()\n298: \n299:         return AnalyzeResponse(\n300:             script=analysis[\"script\"],\n301:             results=analysis[\"results\"],\n302:             report=analysis[\"report\"],\n303:         )\n304: \n305:     except HTTPException:\n306:         raise\n307:     except Exception as e:\n308:         raise HTTPException(status_code=500, detail=str(e))\n309:     finally:\n310:         if pcap_file is not None and local_path is not None:\n311:             try:\n312:                 os.unlink(local_path)\n313:             except OSError:\n314:                 pass\n315: \n316: \n317: # =============================================================================\n318: # CLI Components (design spec: AR-037)\n319: # =============================================================================\n320: \n321: ANALYSIS_SCRIPT = \"\"\"\n322: from scapy.all import rdpcap, IP, TCP, UDP, ICMP, DNS, Raw\n323: import json\n324: import sys\n325: from collections import Counter\n326: \n327: def analyze_pcap(pcap_path, top_n=10, timeline_interval=10.0):\n328:     packets = rdpcap(pcap_path)\n329: \n330:     result = {\n331:         \"file_name\": pcap_path,\n332:         \"total_packets\": len(packets),\n333:         \"duration_seconds\": 0.0,\n334:         \"protocols\": {},\n335:         \"top_source_ips\": [],\n336:         \"top_dest_ips\": [],\n337:         \"timeline\": [],\n338:         \"errors\": []\n339:     }\n340: \n341:     if not packets:\n342:         return result\n343: \n344:     first_ts = float(packets[0].time)\n345:     last_ts = float(packets[-1].time)\n346:     result[\"duration_seconds\"] = last_ts - first_ts\n347: \n348:     proto_counts = Counter()\n349:     src_ips = Counter()\n350:     dst_ips = Counter()\n351:     timeline_buckets = Counter()\n352: \n353:     for pkt in packets:\n354:         ts = float(pkt.time)\n355:         bucket = int((ts - first_ts) / timeline_interval) * timeline_interval + first_ts\n356: \n357:         if pkt.haslayer(TCP):\n358:             proto_counts[\"TCP\"] += 1\n359:             if pkt.haslayer(Raw):\n360:                 proto_counts[\"HTTP\"] += 1\n361:         elif pkt.haslayer(UDP):\n362:             if pkt.haslayer(DNS):\n363:                 proto_counts[\"DNS\"] += 1\n364:             else:\n365:                 proto_counts[\"UDP\"] += 1\n366:         elif pkt.haslayer(ICMP):\n367:             proto_counts[\"ICMP\"] += 1\n368:         else:\n369:             proto_counts[\"Other\"] += 1\n370: \n371:         if pkt.haslayer(IP):\n372:             src_ips[pkt[IP].src] += 1\n373:             dst_ips[pkt[IP].dst] += 1\n374: \n375:         timeline_buckets[bucket] += 1\n376: \n377:     result[\"protocols\"] = dict(proto_counts)\n378:     result[\"top_source_ips\"] = [\n379:         {\"ip\": ip, \"count\": count}\n380:         for ip, count in src_ips.most_common(top_n)\n381:     ]\n382:     result[\"top_dest_ips\"] = [\n383:         {\"ip\": ip, \"count\": count}\n384:         for ip, count in dst_ips.most_common(top_n)\n385:     ]\n386:     result[\"timeline\"] = sorted([\n387:         {\"timestamp\": ts, \"packets\": count}\n388:         for ts, count in timeline_buckets.items()\n389:     ], key=lambda x: x[\"timestamp\"])\n390: \n391:     return result\n392: \n393: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n394:     pcap_file = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else \"/tmp/uploaded.pcap\"\n395:     top_n = int(sys.argv[2]) if len(sys.argv) > 2 else 10\n396:     interval = float(sys.argv[3]) if len(sys.argv) > 3 else 10.0\n397: \n398:     result = analyze_pcap(pcap_file, top_n, interval)\n399:     print(json.dumps(result, indent=2))\n400: \"\"\"\n401: \n402: \n403: def parse_args(args=None):\n404:     \"\"\"Parse CLI arguments.\"\"\"\n405:     parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"PCAP Analyzer Example\")\n406:     parser.add_argument(\"--pcap-file\", default=\"sample_traffic.pcap\",\n407:                         help=\"Path to PCAP file to analyze\")\n408:     parser.add_argument(\"--output\", default=\"analysis_result.json\",\n409:                         help=\"Local path for result output\")\n410:     parser.add_argument(\"--top-n\", type=int, default=10,\n411:                         help=\"Number of top IPs to report\")\n412:     parser.add_argument(\"--timeline-interval\", type=float, default=10.0,\n413:                         help=\"Timeline bucket size in seconds\")\n414:     parser.add_argument(\"--verbose\", action=\"store_true\",\n415:                         help=\"Enable verbose logging\")\n416:     return parser.parse_args(args)\n417: \n418: \n419: def validate_pcap_file(pcap_file: str) -> None:\n420:     \"\"\"Validate that the PCAP file exists locally.\"\"\"\n421:     if not os.path.exists(pcap_file):\n422:         raise FileNotFoundError(f\"PCAP file not found: {pcap_file}\")\n423: \n424: \n425: def check_python_version() -> None:\n426:     \"\"\"Verify Python 3.10+ is available.\"\"\"\n427:     if sys.version_info < (3, 10):\n428:         raise RuntimeError(\n429:             f\"Python 3.10+ required, found {sys.version_info.major}.{sys.version_info.minor}\"\n430:         )\n431: \n432: \n433: def check_tshark_available(client) -> bool:\n434:     \"\"\"Check if tshark is available in the remote sandbox.\"\"\"\n435:     try:\n436:         result = client.execute_command(\"which tshark\")\n437:         return result.strip() != \"\"\n438:     except Exception:\n439:         return False\n440: \n441: \n442: def run_tshark_filter(client, pcap_path: str, filter_expr: str) -> str:\n443:     \"\"\"Run tshark with a display filter on the remote PCAP.\"\"\"\n444:     cmd = f\"tshark -r {pcap_path} -Y '{filter_expr}' -T fields -e ip.src -e ip.dst -e frame.len\"\n445:     return client.execute_command(cmd)\n446: \n447: \n448: def print_analysis_summary(result: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n449:     \"\"\"Print a formatted analysis summary to stdout.\"\"\"\n450:     print(\"PCAP Analysis Complete\")\n451:     print(\"=====================\")\n452:     print(f\"File: {result.get('file_name', 'unknown')}\")\n453:     print(f\"Total packets: {result.get('total_packets', 0)}\")\n454:     print(f\"Duration: {result.get('duration_seconds', 0.0):.2f}s\")\n455:     print()\n456: \n457:     protocols = result.get(\"protocols\", {})\n458:     total = result.get(\"total_packets\", 0)\n459:     if protocols:\n460:         print(\"Protocol Distribution:\")\n461:         for proto, count in sorted(protocols.items(), key=lambda x: -x[1]):\n462:             pct = (count / total * 100) if total > 0 else 0.0\n463:             print(f\"  {proto:<6s}: {count:>4d} ({pct:.1f}%)\")\n464:     else:\n465:         print(\"Protocol Distribution: (none)\")\n466:     print()\n467: \n468:     src_ips = result.get(\"top_source_ips\", [])\n469:     if src_ips:\n470:         print(\"Top Source IPs:\")\n471:         for entry in src_ips:\n472:             print(f\"  {entry['ip']:<18s}: {entry['count']} packets\")\n473:     else:\n474:         print(\"Top Source IPs: (none)\")\n475:     print()\n476: \n477:     dst_ips = result.get(\"top_dest_ips\", [])\n478:     if dst_ips:\n479:         print(\"Top Destination IPs:\")\n480:         for entry in dst_ips:\n481:             print(f\"  {entry['ip']:<18s}: {entry['count']} packets\")\n482:     else:\n483:         print(\"Top Destination IPs: (none)\")\n484: \n485: \n486: def analyze_pcap(\n487:     pcap_file: str,\n488:     output_file: str,\n489:     top_n: int,\n490:     timeline_interval: float,\n491:     verbose: bool,\n492:     router_url: str,\n493: ) -> None:\n494:     \"\"\"Upload PCAP, run analysis, download results.\"\"\"\n495:     from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n496: \n497:     validate_pcap_file(pcap_file)\n498: \n499:     remote_path = f\"/tmp/{os.path.basename(pcap_file)}\"\n500: \n501:     with CodeInterpreterClient(\n502:         name=\"pcap-analyzer\",\n503:         router_url=router_url,\n504:         verbose=verbose,\n505:     ) as client:\n506:         try:\n507:             client.upload_file(pcap_file, remote_path)\n508: \n509:             try:\n510:                 client.run_code(\"python\", \"import scapy\")\n511:             except Exception:\n512:                 if verbose:\n513:                     print(\"Installing scapy in remote sandbox...\")\n514:                 client.run_code(\n515:                     \"python\",\n516:                     \"import subprocess; subprocess.run(['pip', 'install', 'scapy'])\",\n517:                 )\n518: \n519:             script = ANALYSIS_SCRIPT\n520:             result_json = client.run_code(\"python\", script)\n521:             result = json.loads(result_json)\n522: \n523:             if check_tshark_available(client):\n524:                 tshark_result = run_tshark_filter(client, remote_path, \"tcp\")\n525:                 result[\"tshark_tcp_summary\"] = tshark_result\n526: \n527:             with open(output_file, \"w\") as f:\n528:                 json.dump(result, f, indent=2)\n529: \n530:             print_analysis_summary(result)\n531: \n532:         except Exception as e:\n533:             print(f\"Analysis failed: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n534:             sys.exit(1)\n535: \n536: \n537: def main(args=None):\n538:     \"\"\"CLI entry point.\"\"\"\n539:     parsed = parse_args(args)\n540: \n541:     router_url = os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")\n542:     if not router_url:\n543:         print(\"Error: ROUTER_URL environment variable is required\", file=sys.stderr)\n544:         sys.exit(1)\n545: \n546:     analyze_pcap(\n547:         pcap_file=parsed.pcap_file,\n548:         output_file=parsed.output,\n549:         top_n=parsed.top_n,\n550:         timeline_interval=parsed.timeline_interval,\n551:         verbose=parsed.verbose,\n552:         router_url=router_url,\n553:     )\n554: \n555: \n556: if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n557:     if len(sys.argv) > 1 and sys.argv[1] == \"--serve\":\n558:         uvicorn.run(\n559:             \"pcap_analyzer:app\",\n560:             host=SERVER_HOST,\n561:             port=SERVER_PORT,\n562:             reload=SERVER_RELOAD,\n563:         )\n564:     else:\n565:         main()\n\n(End of file - total 565 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"import argparse\nimport json\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport time\nimport tempfile\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, UploadFile, File, Form, HTTPException\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\nimport uvicorn\n\nfrom langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI\nfrom langgraph.prebuilt import create_react_agent\nfrom langchain_core.messages import HumanMessage, AIMessage\n\n# Configuration constants\nAPI_KEY = os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_KEY\")\nAPI_BASE_URL = os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_API_BASE\", \"https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1\")\nMODEL_NAME = os.environ.get(\"OPENAI_MODEL\", \"Qwen/QwQ-32B\")","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py","time":{"start":1775885929638,"end":1775885929644}}}}
