{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885933608,"sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0cd79d0014sMaN2GAokUXyh","messageID":"msg_d7b0cb7b9001v6CJIt7xuuU3uL","sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d340c31905c04833b0b4f979","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/Dockerfile"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/Dockerfile</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: FROM ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim\n2: \n3: WORKDIR /app\n4: \n5: RUN uv venv\n6: \n7: COPY requirements.txt .\n8: RUN uv pip install -r requirements.txt\n9: \n10: COPY sdk-python/agentcube ./agentcube/\n11: COPY pcap_analyzer.py ./\n12: \n13: ENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"\n14: \n15: EXPOSE 8000\n16: \n17: CMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]\n\n(End of file - total 17 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"FROM ghcr.io/astral-sh/uv:python3.12-bookworm-slim\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\nRUN uv venv\n\nCOPY requirements.txt .\nRUN uv pip install -r requirements.txt\n\nCOPY sdk-python/agentcube ./agentcube/\nCOPY pcap_analyzer.py ./\n\nENV PYTHONPATH=\"/app\"\n\nEXPOSE 8000\n\nCMD [\"uv\", \"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/Dockerfile","time":{"start":1775885933600,"end":1775885933607}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885934941,"sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0cdcaf001refgPFmFUvbxOa","messageID":"msg_d7b0cb7b9001v6CJIt7xuuU3uL","sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_e3469fa54cd04ea69f8f7d4a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/deployment.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/deployment.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: apiVersion: apps/v1\n2: kind: Deployment\n3: metadata:\n4:   name: pcap-analyzer\n5:   namespace: default\n6:   labels:\n7:     app: pcap-analyzer\n8: spec:\n9:   replicas: 1\n10:   selector:\n11:     matchLabels:\n12:       app: pcap-analyzer\n13:   template:\n14:     metadata:\n15:       labels:\n16:         app: pcap-analyzer\n17:     spec:\n18:       containers:\n19:         - name: pcap-analyzer\n20:           image: pcap-analyzer:latest\n21:           imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent\n22:           ports:\n23:             - containerPort: 8000\n24:               protocol: TCP\n25:           command: [\"uv\"]\n26:           args: [\"run\", \"pcap_analyzer.py\"]\n27:           resources:\n28:             requests:\n29:               cpu: \"200m\"\n30:               memory: \"100Mi\"\n31:             limits:\n32:               cpu: \"1\"\n33:               memory: \"1Gi\"\n34:           env:\n35:             - name: OPENAI_API_KEY\n36:               valueFrom:\n37:                 secretKeyRef:\n38:                   name: pcap-analyzer-secrets\n39:                   key: openai-api-key\n40:             - name: OPENAI_API_BASE\n41:               value: \"https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1\"\n42:             - name: OPENAI_MODEL\n43:               value: \"Qwen/QwQ-32B\"\n44:             - name: WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\n45:               value: \"\"\n46:             - name: ROUTER_URL\n47:               value: \"\"\n48:             - name: CODEINTERPRETER_NAME\n49:               value: \"my-interpreter\"\n50:             - name: SANDBOX_NAMESPACE\n51:               value: \"default\"\n52:             - name: SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC\n53:               value: \"5\"\n\n(End of file - total 53 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"apiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: Deployment\nmetadata:\n  name: pcap-analyzer\n  namespace: default\n  labels:\n    app: pcap-analyzer\nspec:\n  replicas: 1\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: pcap-analyzer\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: pcap-analyzer\n    spec:\n      containers:\n        - name: pcap-analyzer\n          image: pcap-analyzer:latest","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/deployment.yaml","time":{"start":1775885934930,"end":1775885934940}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775885936237,"sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0ce1fe001CkOEuBA2RWSSz4","messageID":"msg_d7b0cb7b9001v6CJIt7xuuU3uL","sessionID":"ses_284f7aaf6ffe3B81Hd4mt3GYYe","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3128cc338f58431786647414","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # PCAP Analyzer\n2: \n3: A FastAPI service that demonstrates end-to-end usage of the AgentCube SDK for PCAP file analysis via LLM-planned sandbox execution.\n4: \n5: ## Overview\n6: \n7: PCAP Analyzer uses LangChain/LangGraph agents to:\n8: \n9: 1. **Plan**: Generate a Python analysis script based on the PCAP file\n10: 2. **Execute**: Run the script in an AgentCube sandbox environment\n11: 3. **Repair**: Automatically fix scripts that fail execution (with retries)\n12: 4. **Report**: Generate a human-readable analysis report\n13: \n14: ## Architecture\n15: \n16: ```\n17: Client → FastAPI (/analyze) → Planner Agent → SandboxRunner → Reporter Agent → Response\n18:                                     ↓                              ↑\n19:                             Script Generation              Execution Results\n20:                                     ↓                              ↑\n21:                             Repair Agent (on failure) ─────────────┘\n22: ```\n23: \n24: ## Environment Variables\n25: \n26: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n27: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n28: | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | Yes | — | OpenAI-compatible API key |\n29: | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | No | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` | API base URL |\n30: | `OPENAI_MODEL` | No | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` | Model name |\n31: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | No | `my-interpreter` | Code interpreter CR name |\n32: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | No | `default` | Kubernetes namespace for sandboxes |\n33: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | No | `5` | Seconds to wait for sandbox warmup |\n34: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | No | — | AgentCube Workload Manager URL |\n35: | `ROUTER_URL` | No | — | AgentCube Router URL |\n36: \n37: ## Local Development\n38: \n39: ### Prerequisites\n40: \n41: - Python 3.12+\n42: - AgentCube SDK installed or vendored\n43: \n44: ### Install Dependencies\n45: \n46: ```bash\n47: pip install -r requirements.txt\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### Run\n51: \n52: ```bash\n53: export OPENAI_API_KEY=\"your-api-key\"\n54: python pcap_analyzer.py\n55: ```\n56: \n57: The service will start on `http://0.0.0.0:8000`.\n58: \n59: ## Docker Build\n60: \n61: ```bash\n62: # From the repository root (for SDK vendoring)\n63: docker build -t pcap-analyzer:latest -f example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile .\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ## Kubernetes Deployment\n67: \n68: ### Create Secret\n69: \n70: ```bash\n71: kubectl create secret generic pcap-analyzer-secrets \\\n72:   --from-literal=openai-api-key=\"your-api-key\" \\\n73:   -n default\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### Apply Deployment\n77: \n78: ```bash\n79: kubectl apply -f example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ### Access the Service\n83: \n84: Port-forward to access locally:\n85: \n86: ```bash\n87: kubectl port-forward deployment/pcap-analyzer 8000:8000 -n default\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ## API\n91: \n92: ### POST /analyze\n93: \n94: Analyze a PCAP file.\n95: \n96: **Request:**\n97: \n98: - `pcap_file`: Multipart file upload (optional)\n99: - `pcap_path`: Server-side file path (optional)\n100: \n101: At least one of `pcap_file` or `pcap_path` must be provided.\n102: \n103: **Response:**\n104: \n105: ```json\n106: {\n107:   \"script\": \"Generated analysis script\",\n108:   \"results\": [\n109:     {\n110:       \"success\": true,\n111:       \"output\": \"Analysis output...\",\n112:       \"error\": null,\n113:       \"exit_code\": 0\n114:     }\n115:   ],\n116:   \"report\": \"LLM-generated analysis report\"\n117: }\n118: ```\n119: \n120: **Errors:**\n121: \n122: - `400`: Neither `pcap_file` nor `pcap_path` provided\n123: - `422`: Invalid form data\n124: - `500`: Analysis pipeline failure\n\n(End of file - total 124 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# PCAP Analyzer\n\nA FastAPI service that demonstrates end-to-end usage of the AgentCube SDK for PCAP file analysis via LLM-planned sandbox execution.\n\n## Overview\n\nPCAP Analyzer uses LangChain/LangGraph agents to:\n\n1. **Plan**: Generate a Python analysis script based on the PCAP file\n2. **Execute**: Run the script in an AgentCube sandbox environment\n3. **Repair**: Automatically fix scripts that fail execution (with retries)\n4. **Report**: Generate a human-readable analysis report\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nClient → FastAPI (/analyze) → Planner Agent → SandboxRunner → Reporter Agent → Response\n                                    ↓                              ↑\n                            Script Generation              Execution Results\n                                    ↓                              ↑","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/example/pcap_analyzer/README.md","time":{"start":1775885936228,"end":1775885936236}}}}
